00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,000
Once you've read up on the company, you've got to spend some time thinking about yourself.

289
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,000
You've got to prepare to sell yourself to the company.

290
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:51,000
So to sell yourself to really demonstrate them why you are the perfect person for the job.

291
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Right.

292
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:55,000
Because a lot of people think about why they want to work for the company, right?

293
00:12:55,000 --> 00:13:03,000
Because they feel like they're aligned with the core values or the message of the company resonates with them.

294
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:10,000
But what the interviewer really wants to hear is how you, the interviewee, is going to benefit the company.

295
00:13:10,000 --> 00:13:11,000
What are you going to bring to the company?

296
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:15,000
And this is the most important part is to know what are your skills, right?

